The bidder should be either an Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) or Authorized Dealers having been in the business of manufacturing or supplies of Deep Freezers activities during the last 10 years. In support of age of the bidder, the copy of registration/business commencement/certificate issued by the Govt. official/department shall be considered.
If the bidder is an authorized dealer of the OEM, then an authorization for supplies of the required quantities specific to present tender is required to be enclosed as qualifying criteria.

The OEM/ Product Manufacturing Company must have Service Centre in all districts of Bihar & Jharkhand. A list of addresses of OEM?s Service Centre with contact information is to be attached in support of this clause.

The bidder should have annual average turnover of Rs.10 Crore in the same name and style for supply of cold chain items during the last three years. 
The bidder is required to submit the CA?s certificate and Profit & Loss and Balance Sheet for the last three years (2020-21, 2021-22 and 202-23).
The bidder should enclose a copy of PAN and GST Certificate along with the tender documents.
The bidder should enclose the original demand draft for cost of tender as well as EMD drawn in favor of Bihar State Milk Co-operative Federation Ltd. payable at Patna along with the technical bid.
The bidder should enclose the make and model of products offered and catalogue or brochure of the products showing technical specifications of the products offered.
The bidder should enclose an undertaking with regards to non-black listing by any Govt or Semi-Govt or PSU or Cooperative institutions.

The bidder must furnish comprehensive warranty (except consumable) of minimum four years on both the products viz deep freeze & visi-cooler. The bidder would enclose self-declaration for providing the warranty.
